### English Title:
Saudi Arabia Arrests Three for Fraudulent Hajj Campaigns

### English Text Summary:
The Saudi General Security announced the arrest of three individuals for violating border security laws and a Yemeni resident in Mecca for committing fraud by promoting fake Hajj campaigns. These campaigns misled people through social media by offering housing and transportation for pilgrims. The authorities shared a video of the suspects after their arrest and urged citizens and residents to adhere to Hajj regulations and report any violations. The arrested individuals have been detained, and legal actions are being taken against them.

---

